The article discusses the Nuclear Security Summit 2016 Action Plan in support of the Global Partnership Against the Spread of Weapons and Materials of Mass Destruction. The Global Partnership contributes to the development, coordination, implementation, and finance of projects in areas such as nuclear and radiological security. The Action Plan focuses on areas such as enhancing national nuclear security regimes, strengthening nuclear forensics capacities, and the disposition and conversion of nuclear materials. It also emphasizes geographic focus areas and the importance of strengthening cooperation with other international organizations and initiatives. The article advocates for expanding the membership of the Global Partnership, raising its profile with GP and G7 leaders, promoting its work in nuclear security, developing a rapid funding response capability, and enhancing accounting of assistance funding for nuclear security.